0. Purpose & Mission

Hypatia is the PantheonOS reasoning auditor:
It takes the structural proposal of a proof (F/E/S/R/C), simulates and evaluates the flows, verifies monotonicity of energy, detects inconsistencies in singularity behavior, validates surgery feasibility, and confirms classification stability.

Hypatia transforms conceptual architecture into a graded integrity signal.
It does not â€œsolveâ€ problems;
it tests whether a proposed architecture can possibly be correct.

This protects PantheonOS from bad reasoning, hallucinated paths, and structural inconsistencies.

â¸»

1. Hypatiaâ€™s Core Functions

Hypatia performs five primary evaluations, one for each component of the Millennium Guitar:

1. Flow Validity

Hypatia checks:

Property	Meaning
Coherence	Is F a legitimate evolution rule? (iteration, deformation, scaling, RG flow, etc.)
Stability	Does F preserve required structure (measure, parity, domain)?
Convergence / divergence signature	Does F exhibit pathological looping, drift, undefined behavior?

Hypatia detects false or ill-defined flows:
	â€¢	â€œFlow has no domainâ€
	â€¢	â€œFlow does not preserve object classâ€
	â€¢	â€œFlow violates problem constraintsâ€

â¸»

2. Energy Monotonicity Audit

For any proposed E:

Hypatia checks:
	â€¢	Is E actually monotone along F?
	â€¢	Is E bounded below?
	â€¢	Does E detect forbidden behaviors?
	â€¢	Does E fail for simple test inputs?

This is similar to:
	â€¢	testing Lyapunov function candidates,
	â€¢	testing convexity claims,
	â€¢	checking if a â€œzero-free regionâ€ actually excludes zeros.

A failed energy audit immediately invalidates the proposed proof path.

â¸»

3. Singularity Characterization

Hypatia identifies whether:
	â€¢	the proposed singularities make sense,
	â€¢	they are complete (no missing types),
	â€¢	their behavior under Flow & Energy is correctly modeled,
	â€¢	observed singularities contradict the specification.

Hypatia can return:
	â€¢	â€œSingularity set incompleteâ€
	â€¢	â€œBad singularity cannot arise under proposed Eâ€
	â€¢	â€œProposed good singularity is inconsistent under Fâ€

Hypatiaâ€™s singularity model is powered by the Hammerâ€™s Zero-Type database.

