4. Surgery Feasibility Check

Hypatia evaluates:
	â€¢	Is surgery (R) legal?
	â€¢	Does it use only invariants guaranteed by E?
	â€¢	Does surgery disconnect or contradict Flow preservation?
	â€¢	Does R require unproven assumptions?

Hypatia refuses magical leaps.

Invalid surgeries produce:
	â€¢	â€œSurgery requires forbidden transformationâ€
	â€¢	â€œSurgery violates measure preservationâ€
	â€¢	â€œCut cannot be constructed in this topologyâ€

This shields the system from fabrications or hallucinated constructions.

