3. RIS: Reasoning Integrity Score

Hypatia outputs a single meta-metric:

\textbf{RIS} \in [0,1].

RIS measures:
	â€¢	structural coherence,
	â€¢	flow validity,
	â€¢	energy correctness,
	â€¢	singularity completeness,
	â€¢	surgery feasibility,
	â€¢	classification inevitability.

RIS â‰¥ 0.9:
Architecture is structurally sound.

0.7 â‰¤ RIS < 0.9:
Plausible route; refinement needed.

RIS < 0.7:
Architecture internally unstable or incoherent.

RIS does not prove the theorem â€”
it evaluates the structural correctness of the proposed argument.

